\section{Financial Impact}

\[
\text{Waste} = \frac{\text{Bound Estimate}}{\text{Exact Probability}}
\]

At $\lambda = 500$:
\begin{itemize}
\item Chernoff: $10.7\times$
\item Chebyshev: $6422\times$
\item Markov: $107039\times$
\end{itemize}

\section{Final Conclusion}

\begin{itemize}
\item System failure depends on tail probability $P(X \geq k)$
\item Exact computation is often infeasible
\item Use bounds:
\[
\text{Markov} \rightarrow \text{Chebyshev} \rightarrow \text{Chernoff}
\]
\item Better information $\Rightarrow$ tighter bounds
\item Loose bounds $\Rightarrow$ financial waste
\item Tight bounds $\Rightarrow$ efficient system design
\end{itemize}

